Package it.polimi.se2019.model

Class NormalMatch

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.se2019.model.Match
      • it.polimi.se2019.model.NormalMatch
  • public class NormalMatch
extends Match
    Contains and supports the information for the flow of a Match in standard mode. Supports the killShotTrack and a custom parsing of winners, compared to the general Match.

      • scoreDeadShot

        public void scoreDeadShot​(Player player)
        Score a deadShot to player. The player that gave the kill shot gets added to the killShotTrack. If an overkill took place, the player that overkilled gets added to the track and a mark gets added to the overkiller.
        Specified by:
        scoreDeadShot in class Match
        Parameters:
        player - who got the killshot

      • getWinners

        public java.util.List<Player> getWinners()
        Parse the winners of the current Game, at the end of it.
      • It scores the players in the game.
      • It scores the killShotTrack, sorting looking at the players that gave the more shots.
      • It checks the online players, and the order of the killings to create the list of winners.
Specified by:
getWinners in class Match
Returns:
winning players
